The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 March is 40,878 (4,731.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 March, there were 271 new confirmed cases (31.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 March, there were 368 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 26% (97 fewer cases).
